    "body" : "On Java8+ has Optional class in jdk. Example of usage Optional.ofNullable(x).orElse(-1). Other good usage of usage Optional is method map. Let say there object a which is equivalent of json object: &quot;a&quot;: {&quot;b&quot;:{&quot;c&quot;:1}}. To read c value can be such construction like: Optional.ofNullable(a).map(a-&gt;a.b).map(b-&gt;b.c).orElse(-1). Is much ugly literal syntax than C#, but it is better option that using cascading operator ?:"
