      "comment_id" : 41801380,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The real issue with a solution like this is that it sacrifices the null coalesces lazy evaluation. Since all of the values have to be passed to <code>Objects.firstNonNull</code>, any functions you have passed will be evaluated. This makes it potentially far more computationally expensive than C#&#39;s <code>??</code>."
