    "question_id" : 5223044,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Short answer: <strong>no</strong></p>\n\n<p>The best you can do is to create a static utility method (so that it can be imported using <code>import static</code> syntax)</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static &lt;T&gt; T coalesce(T one, T two)\n{\n    return one != null ? one : two;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The above is equivalent to Guava's method <code>firstNonNull</code> by @ColinD, but that can be extended more in general</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static &lt;T&gt; T coalesce(T... params)\n{\n    for (T param : params)\n        if (param != null)\n            return param;\n    return null;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
